<subSubSection pageId="302" pageNumber="303" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="302" pageNumber="303">
This rarely collected species is known from scattered localities in the southern parts of the Prairie Provinces (Lindroth 1961a: 147; Bousquet 1988a: 373), southeastern Oregon (Harney County, CNC), northwestern (Pershing County, MCZ) and west-central (Bechtel et al. 1983: 474) Nevada, north-central Utah (Utah County, USNM), and eastern California (Fall 1925: 310, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1925" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desertus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Dyschirius desertus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Inyo and Plumas Counties, CAS).
</paragraph>
